# GitHub Copilot is an AI-powered code completion tool that helps developers write code faster and with fewer errors.
# It suggests whole lines or blocks of code as you type, based on the context of the current file and your coding style.

# To use GitHub Copilot, you need to install the extension in your code editor and sign in with your GitHub account.
# Once installed, you can start typing and see suggestions from Copilot, which you can accept, reject, or modify as needed.

# GitHub Copilot supports a wide range of programming languages and frameworks, making it a versatile tool for developers of all kinds.